name: Filenet
description: Filenet (FN) describes itself as a public chain of distributed storage applications that has launched its mainnet. It claims to be the world's first public chain of distributed storage applications that uses a DPOS - POC consensus mechanism. Filenet is committed to storing, distributing valuable content, and rewarding miners that contribute to idle bandwidth and storage. The mission of Filenet is to establish a robust distributed data service system by connecting idle storage and allowing internet-connected storage devices to participate in mining.
